DataElement.preferredName: Electrospray Ionization Instrumentation Ionization Source Identifier java.lang.Long
DataElement.preferredDefinition: A procedure used in mass spectrometry analysis. Means of delivering nonvolatile analytes into the gas phase for mass analysis. Best used on molecules which are charged in solution or readily accept a charge. Particularly well suited to the analysis of biomolecules. Can be used to probe tertiary structure and non-covalent interactions (from NCSU Mass Spectrometry Facility web site):Any object, or item of electrical or electronic equipment, which is designed to carry out a specific function or set of functions._A device that converts a sample into an ion stream.:One or more characters used to identify, name, or characterize the nature, properties, or contents of a thing._Generic value domain for a primitive java dataype that is a long integer (64-bit two's complement).
